Framed Prints

Adorn your home with elegance and history with our Framed Print of Maria Josepha of Saxony, Dauphine of France. This stunning artwork is inspired by a portrait painted by the renowned French Rococo artist, Maurice Quentin de La Tour. Depicting Maria Josepha from her time as Dauphine of France, starting at the age of fifteen, this print captures the grace and beauty of the Saxon princess in an exquisite and intricately detailed design. Bring a touch of royal history into your space with this timeless and captivating piece.

Photo Prints

Experience the elegance and sophistication of the past with our exquisite Maria Josepha of Saxony photographic print from the Media Storehouse collection. This stunning portrait, inspired by the original work of Maurice Quentin de La Tour, showcases the young Dauphine of France from the age of fifteen, capturing her grace and beauty during her marriage to Louis de France. Transport yourself back in time with this authentic and captivating piece of art history, perfect for adding a touch of timeless charm to your home or office decor.

Poster Prints

Step back in time with our exquisite Maria Josepha of Saxony Poster Print. This elegant portrait, inspired by the original painting by Maurice Quentin de La Tour, captures the youthful beauty and grace of Maria Josepha during her tenure as Dauphine of France. A true masterpiece of French Rococo art, this print is a must-have for history buffs, art enthusiasts, and those who appreciate the beauty of the past. Bring the opulence and sophistication of the 18th century into your home or office with this stunning, high-quality poster print.

Jigsaw Puzzles

Discover the captivating history of Maria Josepha of Saxony, Dauphine of France, brought to life through the intricate details of our Jigsaw Puzzles from Media Storehouse. This beautiful puzzle, inspired by Maurice Quentin de La Tour's iconic 1760 portrait, invites you to immerse yourself in the elegance and grace of the 18th century. Piece together the rich history of Maria Josepha, from her time as a young dauphine at the age of fifteen through her marriage to Louis de France. Each puzzle piece is meticulously crafted, providing a satisfying challenge for puzzle enthusiasts of all ages.
